<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id907a9f18-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s4602"><num value="4602">§ 4602.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">As used in this chapter, the term—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id907a9f19-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s4602/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> “Institute” means the United States Institute of Peace established by this chapter; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id907a9f1a-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s4602/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> “Board” means the Board of Directors of the Institute.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id907a9f1b-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/525/tXVII/s1703">Pub. L. 98–525, title XVII, § 1703</ref>, <date date="1984-10-19">Oct. 19, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/2651">98 Stat. 2651</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
